FG-391 — Cert “One-Screen” QP Card (QP • Split • Relief)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Fit the entire petition on one screen.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Three boxes: Question Presented (≤15 words) • Split grid (3 rows) • Relief ladder (Grant/GVR/Hold). Label neutral.
	•	📝 Assignment: Build your QP card and file as a notice if allowed.
	•	✅ Model Response: “QP: Must courts make factor findings? Split: 2d v. 9th. Relief: Grant; or GVR; or Hold.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: One screen is how Justices skim.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A phone-sized card with three stacked boxes.

⸻

FG-392 — Cert Pin Map (Case • Cite • Holding)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Cert persuasion runs on three holdings, side by side.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Map: Case • Cite • Holding (≤10 words); three rows; mirror in petition text.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 3-row pin map for your cert petition.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Winter, 555 U.S. 7 — factor-tied findings required. Doe, 2022 — not required. Smith, 2019 — unclear.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Maps beat adjectives.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A grid of three holdings, pinned like index cards.

⸻

FG-393 — Cert OA Card (If Granted)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Prepare the OA card now; don’t wait for grant.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: One screen: Q • Std • 2 pins • Relief; hash it; file a “lodged demonstrative” if permitted.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft your cert OA card and hash it.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Q: Must courts make findings? Std: de novo. Pins: Dkt 18:2; Tab 3 p.2. Relief: remand 21d.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Preparedness = credibility.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A palm card with four crisp blocks.

⸻

FG-394 — Cert Amicus Invitation (Target • Q • Deadline)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Amici amplify when specific and early.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: One-page invitation: identify target groups; frame the Question Presented; state amicus deadline; attach petition hash; neutral tone.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 7-line amicus invite for your petition.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Question Presented: Must courts make factor findings? Amicus briefs due 10/01. Petition hash ….”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Invite with clarity, not desperation.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: An open envelope with “QP” and a deadline chip.

⸻

FG-395 — Cert Amicus Coordination Note (No Duplication)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Multiple amici should divide lanes, not echo.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Short note: “Amicus A covers split; Amicus B covers policy; both adopt core relief text.” Attach a duplication certification.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 6-line coordination note between two amici.
	•	✅ Model Response: “A: split map. B: equities. Both adopt relief ladder. Duplication certification attached.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Harmony earns credibility.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: Two arrows pointing to one relief card.

⸻

FG-396 — Cert “Two-Pin Summary”
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Boil your petition down to two pins + order.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Pin 1 = split case; Pin 2 = your record gap; Order = relief ladder.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a two-pin summary card in ≤40 words.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Pin 1: 2d Cir. says no findings. Pin 2: ‘Not reached’ (Dkt 18:2). Relief: Grant or GVR.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Two pins survive cert pool memos.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: Two dots linked into a SCOTUS order.

⸻

FG-397 — Cert Public Page (Docs • Hashes • Status)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Build a public microsite page with docs + hashes + next date.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Table: Date • Doc • SHA-256 • Link • Status; update within 24h.
	•	📝 Assignment: Export your cert index as HTML/PDF with 3 rows.
	•	✅ Model Response: “09/01 — Petition filed (sha …). 09/02 — Appendix (sha …). Next: response due 10/01.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Public timelines protect you.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A clean table with fingerprint icons.

⸻

FG-398 — Cert Reply Hygiene (≤3 Pages, Fit-Only)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: A cert reply is for fit, not flourish.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: ≤3 pages; show split misfit (2 rows); pin your record gap; end with relief ladder.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 3-page reply skeleton for your cert petition.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Resp: circuits don’t split. Reply: Table shows 2d v. 9th. Record gap remains (Dkt 18:2). Relief: grant/GVR/hold.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Replies should shrink, not sprawl.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A slim reply card with a “3p” badge.

⸻

FG-399 — Cert Amicus Bank (Ready-to-File One-Pagers)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Stock amici with ready one-pagers tied to your QP.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Provide template: QP • Split • Pin • Relief; hash; deliver early. Each amicus customizes policy voice but adopts your relief.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft one amicus one-pager template.
	•	✅ Model Response: “QP: Must courts make factor findings? Split: 2d v. 9th. Pin: ‘Not reached’ (Dkt 18:2). Relief: grant or GVR.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Templates multiply voices.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: Multiple one-page sheets fanning from one petition tile.

⸻

FG-400 — Cert “Closeout Kit” (Zip + Release Note)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Close every cert phase with a zip + note.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: ZIP root: Petition.pdf • Appendix.pdf • Amicus invites • CHECKSUMS.txt • ReleaseNote.md; hash; post mirrors.
	•	📝 Assignment: Build your cert closeout kit and post with hash + note.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Release v1—Cert kit posted; Petition (sha …), Appendix (sha …); CHECKSUMS.txt; mirrors aligned.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Closure is memory.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A ribboned ZIP folder with a fingerprint footer.
